    {
      "content": "Add an A record for your custom domain",
      "pos": [
        1358,
        1396
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"understanding-records\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Understand CNAME and A records",
      "pos": [
        1427,
        1493
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "CNAME (or alias records) and A records both allow you to associate a domain name with a website, however they each work differently.",
      "pos": [
        1500,
        1632
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "CNAME or Alias record",
      "pos": [
        1637,
        1658
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A CNAME record maps a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>specific<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> domain, such as <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>contoso.com<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>www.contoso.com<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>, to a canonical domain name.",
      "pos": [
        1660,
        1776
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In this case, the canonical domain name is the either the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>&amp;lt;myapp&gt;.azurewebsites.net<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> domain name of your Azure website or the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>&amp;lt;myapp&gt;.trafficmgr.com<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> domain name of your Traffic Manager profile.",
      "pos": [
        1777,
        1983
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once created, the CNAME creates an alias for the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>&amp;lt;myapp&gt;.azurewebsites.net<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>&amp;lt;myapp&gt;.trafficmgr.com<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> domain name.",
      "pos": [
        1984,
        2111
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The CNAME entry will resolve to the IP address of your <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>&amp;lt;myapp&gt;.azurewebsites.net<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>&amp;lt;myapp&gt;.trafficmgr.com<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> domain name automatically, so if the IP address of the website changes, you do not have to take any action.",
      "pos": [
        2112,
        2340
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Some domain registrars only allow you to map subdomains when using a CNAME record, such as www.contoso.com, and not root names, such as contoso.com.",
      "pos": [
        2344,
        2505
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information on CNAME records, see the documentation provided by your registrar, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CNAME_record\"&gt;</ph>the Wikipedia entry on CNAME record<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>, or the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;a href=\"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1035\"&gt;</ph>IETF Domain Names - Implementation and Specification<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> document.",
      "pos": [
        2506,
        2806
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A record",
      "pos": [
        2811,
        2819
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An A record maps a domain, such as <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>contoso.com<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>www.contoso.com<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>or a wildcard domain<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept> such as <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>\\*.contoso.com<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>, to an IP address.",
      "pos": [
        2821,
        2964
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the case of an Azure Website, either the virtual IP of the service or a specific IP address that you purchased for your website.",
      "pos": [
        2965,
        3096
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "So the main benefit of an A record over a CNAME record is that you can have one entry that uses a wildcard, such as *<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>.contoso.com<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, which would handle requests for multiple sub-domains such as <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>mail.contoso.com<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>login.contoso.com<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>, or <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>www.contso.com<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3097,
        3360
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Since an A record is mapped to a static IP address, it cannot automatically resolve changes to the IP address of your website.",
      "pos": [
        3364,
        3503
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An IP address for use with A records is provided when you configure custom domain name settings for your website; however, this value may change if you delete and recreate your website, or change the website mode to back to free.",
      "pos": [
        3504,
        3733
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> A records cannot be used for load balancing with Traffic Manager.",
      "pos": [
        3737,
        3815
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Controlling Azure Web Sites Traffic with Azure Traffic Manager<ept id=\"p1\">][trafficmanager]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3816,
        3923
      ]
    },
    {
